4. Server Setup

The frontend is hosted separately from the Jitsi backend.

Example server structure:

/var/www/custom-jitsi

Served by:

nginx

Typical stack:

Ubuntu Linux
nginx
Jitsi Meet
Jitsi Videobridge
Prosody
Jicofo

Websockets are enabled for videobridge communication.

Example configuration:

/etc/jitsi/videobridge/jvb.conf
videobridge {
    websockets {
        enabled = true
        tls = true
    }
}
5. Integration With Calendar Systems

The video consultation system integrates with external calendar software.

The calendar system generates secure session URLs using a REST API.

Example workflow:

Calendar system creates a consultation appointment

Backend generates session tokens

Two URLs are created

Example:

https://video.domain/advisor/<token>
https://video.domain/client/<token>

These URLs are sent to participants via:

email

calendar invitation

Users join directly through their browser.

6. Functional Requirements

The consultation system must support the following features.

Video & Audio

Participants must be able to:

enable / disable camera

enable / disable microphone

communicate using WebRTC

Screen Sharing

Participants can share their screen when needed.

Chat (Consultation Notes)

Participants can exchange text messages.

Chat messages function as consultation notes.

File Exchange

Files can be shared through the chat.

Examples:

PDFs

images

documents

All files must be temporary.

7. Forbidden Features

Several default Jitsi features must be disabled or removed.

The system must NOT support:

meeting recording
background images
virtual backgrounds
more than two participants

The UI must not expose these features.

8. Data Retention Requirements

For privacy reasons, no data may persist after the meeting.

The server must automatically delete:

chat history
uploaded files
temporary session data

This is required for GDPR compliance.

9. User Flow
Step 1 — User Opens Session Link

User opens the consultation link.

Example:

https://video.domain/session/<token>
Step 2 — Device Selection

User sees a pre-join screen.

User selects:

microphone
camera
speaker
Step 3 — Join Meeting

User clicks:

Join

The user joins the video consultation.

Step 4 — Consultation Interface

The interface contains:

large video of the other participant
small self preview
microphone control
camera control
leave button
chat panel
connection quality indicator
Step 5 — Session End

When the call ends the user sees an end screen.

Example:

Session ended
Thank you for using the consultation service

This screen can be customized.

